# MIRAIKANAI baseline (Cursor rule)

- **Authority:** [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) is the shared baseline; resolve conflicts in favor of `AGENTS.md`.
- **Automation:** Use **PowerShell 7** only: `pwsh -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File tools/<script>.ps1`. Do not use Windows PowerShell 5.1 or ad hoc `package.json` scripts for repo tasks.
- **`tools/*.ps1` edits:** Follow **`AGENTS.md` → Repository command entrypoints** for PSScriptAnalyzer-friendly patterns (automatic variables, `ShouldProcess` on host-mutating helpers, `Write-Information` vs `Write-Host`, non-empty `catch`, approved verbs such as `ConvertTo-*` over `Normalize-*`). Run **`Invoke-ScriptAnalyzer`** on touched scripts when the module is installed.
- **Expanded procedures:** [`docs/agent-operational-reference.md`](../../docs/agent-operational-reference.md) (validation matrix, editor shell details, plan lifecycle, game lanes).
- **Skills:** Thin pointers under [`.cursor/skills/`](../../.cursor/skills/); canonical bodies under [`.claude/skills/`](../../.claude/skills/) and [`.agents/skills/`](../../.agents/skills/).
- **Agent-surface drift check:** Before finishing implementation, improvements, bug fixes, refactors, or architecture/toolchain/workflow/validation/packaging changes, compare the changed behavior/API/workflow against owning surfaces and update stale durable guidance across `AGENTS.md`, skills, rules, subagents, manifests, schemas, and validation checks in the same task; do not load every surface when no durable guidance changed.
- **Parallel work:** Prefer Codex app Worktree/Handoff or Claude Code `--worktree` / subagent `isolation: worktree`; keep `.worktrees/` and `.claude/worktrees/` ignored, run `pwsh -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File tools/prepare-worktree.ps1` in manual linked worktrees, and clean merged task work with `pwsh -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File tools/remove-merged-worktree.ps1 -WorktreePath <path> [-BaseRef origin/main] [-BaseBranch main] [-Remote origin] [-LocalCheckoutPath <path>] [-DeleteLocalBranch]` so the local base checkout fast-forwards before guarded cleanup and standard roots can come from Git main worktree porcelain records.
- **Publishing:** Follow official GitHub Flow: commit validated task-owned phases on topic branches, inspect or refresh remote state before pushing, push validated checkpoints for backup/CI/review/handoff rather than by commit count, keep one PR per focused capability/gap-cluster/milestone, open an early draft PR for large slices, rely on required reviews/checks plus GitHub auto-merge, and never push directly to the default branch.
- **Efficiency:** Keep reads, tests, phases, and validation scoped to the smallest behavior/API/validation boundary, but keep plan files at capability/gap-cluster/milestone scale rather than PR/task-count scale; prefer clean breaking implementation over compatibility shims, and do not weaken official best practices or validation evidence for speed. Docs/agent/rules/subagent-only PRs should use lightweight static validation, not unrelated Windows/MSVC, macOS, or full repository clang-tidy lanes.
- **Instruction size:** Keep `AGENTS.md` as concise baseline guidance; place reusable workflows in skills and long procedures in docs.
- **User language:** Respond in Japanese when the user writes Japanese; keep code, paths, and API names in ASCII.
